https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/concurrency/procthread.html

Thread of control -> thread

Threads exist within a process — every process has at least one thread.
Threads share the process's resources, including memory and open files.

Multithreaded execution is an essential feature of the Java platform.
Every application has at least one thread — or several

Thread states:
1. New -> new Thread();
2. Runnable -> yield() -> static method
3. Blocked
4. Waiting
5. Timed waiting
6. Terminated

Runnable thread: